                <head>No. 117.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Osborn</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 23, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 89.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herein for your information a copy of
                    a late instruction<note n="*" xml:id="d117fn1">See Mr. Evarts’s instruction to
                        Mr. Adams, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_78">page
                        78</ref>.</note> sent to Mr. Adams, the newly appointed minister of the
                    United States to Bolivia, respecting a proposition of Chili, touching an
                    exchange between those countries of prisoners of war.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
